Package: lighthouseR
Type: Package
Title:Start and Retrieve Data from 'Lighthouse' in 'R'
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Daniel Schmeh
Maintainer: Daniel Schmeh <danielschmeh@gmail.com>
Description: Allows you to retrieve 'Lighthouse' Data and install 'Lighthouse' on your locale machine.
    'Lighthouse' will analyze the Page you specific in the request. 'Lighthouse' will open a new 'Chrome' Window and run various tests.
    The output you will get consists of 5 numeric values: 'Progressive Web App', 'Performance', 'Accessibility', 'Best Practice's and 'SEO'. Each a number between 0 (very bad) and 100 (perfect).
    Additional to this you will get a 'HTML-file' in your Workspace containing all results of the 'Lighthouse' test. So you can have a deeper look in various parts.
    You can find more information about 'Lighthouse' here: <https://developers.google.com/web/tools/lighthouse/>.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1.9000
Imports:
    stringr,
    utils
SystemRequirements: lighthouseR requires Node 6 or later.     
